IRS990.Desc: THE GIRL SCOUT LEADERSHIP EXPERIENCE - THE GIRL SCOUT LEADERSHIP EXPERIENCE PREPARES GIRLS TO BE FUTURE LEADERS IN THEIR FAMILIES, COMMUNITIES AND BUSINESSES BY COMBINING SKILLS AND EDUCATION ON PROBLEM SOLVING, CONFLICT RESOLUTION, RESILIENCE, DIVERSITY AND TEAM BUILDING WITH EXPOSURE TO STEM (SCIENCE, TECHNOLOGY, ENGINEERING AND MATH) FINANCIAL LITERACY, ENVIRONMENTAL STEWARDSHIP, ADVOCACY AND HEALTH. OUR PROGRAM REFLECTS THE BELIEF THAT A LEADER UNDERSTAND HERSELF AND HER VALUES (DISCOVER), CARES ABOUT, INSPIRES AND TEAMS WITH OTHERS (CONNECT) TO MAKE THE WORLD A BETTER PLACE (TAKE ACTION). DURING THE YEAR ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2018, THE GIRL SCOUTS LEADERSHIP EXPERIENCE TOUCHED OVER 8,862 GIRLS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE GIRL SCOUT CAMP PROGRAM AND OUTDOOR EXPERIENCE - THE GIRL SCOUT CAMP PROGRAM AND OUTDOOR EXPERIENCE PROVIDES A PLACE TO EMBRACE AND ENCOUNTER THE NATURAL ENVIRONMENT, PROMOTE COMMUNITY, TEACH CRITICAL THINKING AND CREATE FUTURE LEADERS. GIRL SCOUTS OF NORTHEASTERN NEW YORK OFFERS YEAR-ROUND CAMP EXPERIENCES THAT PROMOTE THESE ESSENTIAL SKILLS IN AN OUTDOOR SETTING. DURING THE YEAR ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2018 OVER 3,500 GIRLS AND ADULTS GAINED THE SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE THEY NEEDED TO BUILD A SOLID FOUNDATION FOR SELF-MANAGEMENT, HEALTHY LIFESTYLES AND TEAM BUILDING THROUGH DAY AND WEEKEND EVENTS AND SUMMER DAY AND RESIDENTIAL CAMPS. THE GIRL SCOUTS OF NORTHEASTERN NEW YORK OPERATES 5 CAMPS IN ITS 15 COUNTY JURISDICTION.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: VOLUNTEER DEVELOPMENT AND SUPPORT - GIRL SCOUTING IS DELIVERED PRIMARILY BY ADULT VOLUNTEERS WITH COUNCIL RESOURCES DEDICATED TO SUPPORTING THE RECRUITMENT, EDUCATION AND RETENTION OF VOLUNTEERS. DURING THE YEAR ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2018, 4,432 ADULT VOLUNTEERS HELPED BRING THE LEADERSHIP EXPERIENCE TO THOUSANDS OF GIRLS. WITHOUT OUR VOLUNTEER EDUCATION AND SUPPORT RESOURCES, GIRL SCOUTS OF NORTHEASTERN NEW YORK WOULD NOT BE ABLE TO DELIVER ITS PREMIER PROGRAMS TO MORE THAN 8,862 GIRLS ANNUALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE UTILIZED TO PROVIDE NEED-BASED ASSISTANCE TO GIRLS FOR VARIOUS ORGANIZATION ACTIVITIES, MAINTENANCE OF THE ORGANIZATION'S PHYSICAL PROPERTY/FACILITIES, AND SUPPORTING SPECIFIED PROGRAM OBJECTIVES.

GSNENY FILES FORM 990 ANNUALLY WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. WHEN ANNUAL RETURNS ARE FILED, SOME TAX POSITIONS TAKEN ARE HIGHLY CERTAIN TO BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE TAXING AUTHORITIES, WHILE OTHER TAX POSITIONS ARE SUBJECT TO UNCERTAINTY ABOUT THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION OR AMOUNT OF THE POSITION'S TAX BENEFIT THAT WOULD ULTIMATELY BE SUSTAINED. MANAGEMENT EVALUATED GSNENY'S TAX POSITIONS AND CONCLUDED THAT GSNENY HAD TAKEN NO TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRED ADJUSTMENT OR DISCLOSURE IN ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2018 AND 2017.
UNREALIZED GAINS ON BENEFICIAL INTERESTS IN PERPETUAL TRUSTS, NET 142,046.

GSNENY HAS ESTABLISHED AN APPLICATION REVIEW PROCESS FOR ALL REQUESTS FOR FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE. FOR REQUESTS FOR MEMBERSHIP REGISTRATION, UNIFORMS AND PROGRAMS $75 AND UNDER : GSNENY USES 130% OF THE POVERTY LEVEL AS THE CRITERIA FOR ELIGIBILITY. WE FILE A COPY OF ALL APPLICATIONS AND MAINTAIN A SPREADSHEET INDICATING THE AMOUNT OF EACH AWARD AS WELL AS THE AMOUNT OF EACH MERCHANDISE VOUCHER THAT IS ACTUALLY REDEEMED. FOR PROGRAMS (INCLUDING TRAVEL AND CAMP) OVER $75, APPLICATIONS ARE REVIEWED BY THE GIRL GRANT COMMITTEE* AND CRITERIA THAT ARE CONSIDERED IN DETERMINING THE NEED OF THE APPLICANT INCLUDE: - HOUSEHOLD SIZE AND MAKE-UP (# OF ADULTS AND DEPENDENTS) - HOUSEHOLD INCOME (GROSS ANNUAL) - PARTICIPATION IN FEDERAL SCHOOL MEAL PROGRAMS - DESCRIPTION OF WHY A GIRL GRANT IS NECESSARY - AMOUNT PARENT/APPLICANT IS CONTRIBUTING COMPARED TO THE TOTAL COST OF THE PROGRAM THE GIRL GRANT COMMITTEE AWARDS GRANTS IN ORDER TO SUPPORT THE GREATEST NUMBER OF GIRLS IN NEED, WITHIN THE RESTRICTIONS OF THE FUNDING THAT IS AVAILABLE. AFTER A PROGRAM, THE REGISTRAR DEPARTMENT AND GIRL GRANT STAFF LIAISON ADJUST THE TRACKING SPREADSHEET AS NEEDED FOR AMOUNT OF AWARDS USED (FOR GIRLS WHO CANCELED, DID NOT SHOW UP AT A PROGRAM, OR USED LESS THAN THEY WERE AWARDED) AND PROVIDE A REPORT TO THE FINANCE DEPARTMENT AND FUND DEVELOPMENT DEPARTMENT FOR FUNDS USED FOR REPORTING AND AUDITING PURPOSES. *THE GIRL GRANT COMMITTEE IS A VOLUNTEER COMMITTEE COMPRISED OF COMMUNITY MEMBERS FROM THE GREATER CAPITAL REGION AND ARE NOT AFFILIATED WITH ANY TROOP.
